reviews.title: Taste an excellent Champagne
reviews.text:
We booked a table for 4 people to be sure to find a seat... after our arrival we were very well received and served at best. We chose to try the tastings of 3 types of champagne. Quality price excellent.
The bar room is very nice. Nearby you can make a visit to the shop.
The only flaw appetizers to eat are expensive and nothing big. Overall though a great experience.
Free parking available on site

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. articleContent.title: Netflix host Jo Franco shows us her Rio

seoInfo.metaDescription: As one of the hosts of Netflix's Amazing Vacation Rentals, Jo Franco takes viewers around the world. But for all her globetrotting, Rio de Janeiro is the place she goes back to again and again. We get all her tips for where to go and what to do.

tripContent.title: Santa Fe: heritage & history on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Looking for adventure on the original Route 66? Santa Fe, the oldest state capital, is a must-stop for history buffs. The city, founded in 1610, is older than the United States—but the area has been populated for well over a thousand years. With so much history and heritage, you'll want to allow plenty of time to explore the best of the Southwest—so here are 12 suggestions for things to see, do, and learn.

tripContent.title: A guide to Orlando Pride events and hotspots for LGBTQ+ travelers
tripContent.description: "Orlando is serving up way more than just theme parks. Join me, Meg Ten Eyck, on an adventure that's all about incredible food, outdoor thrills, and queer celebration. With LGBTQ-owned businesses to support, a vibrant culinary scene, and unique experiences like paddleboarding, kayaking with manatees, and a sunset airboat ride, there’s no shortage of excitement. With Orlando Pride and legendary lesbian events, this city thrives on community, connection, and unforgettable moments. Whether you're enjoying the food, the culture, or the wild adventures, Orlando is all about making memories." - Meg Ten Eyc
